<h2>sl-simple-modal</h2>
<p class="lead">A simple modal component used to wrap content in. Based on <a href="http://getbootstrap.com/javascript/#modals">Bootstrap - Modals</a>.</p>

<hr>

<h3>Example</h3>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-6">
        <h6>Template</h6>
        <pre>\{{#sl-simple-modal
    id="testModal"
    show=showModal
    title="Test Modal"}}
    &lt;p&gt;Hello world!&lt;/p&gt;
\{{/sl-simple-modal}}</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="col-lg-6">
        <h6>Click to Show Component</h6>
        {{sl-button action="openModal" label="Open Modal"}}
    </div>
</div>


{{#sl-simple-modal id="testModal" show=showModal title="Test Modal"}}
    <p>Hello World!</p>
{{/sl-simple-modal}}


<hr>

<h3>Properties</h3>

<div class="list-group">
    {{#property-text name="accept" type="function"}}
        Action to call when accept button is clicked.
    {{/property-text}}

    {{#property-text name="acceptText" type="string" default="\"Accept\""}}
        Text label for the accept button.
    {{/property-text}}

    {{#property-text name="cancelText" type="string" default="\"Cancel\""}}
        Text label for the cancel button.
    {{/property-text}}

    {{#property-text name="close" type="function"}}
        Action to call when one of the close buttons is clicked.
    {{/property-text}}

    {{#property-text name="show" type="boolean"}}
        Bound property to open/show the modal.
    {{/property-text}}

    {{#property-text name="title" type="string" default="null"}}
        Title text at the top of the modal window.
    {{/property-text}}
</div>

<hr>

<h3>Aria support</h3>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-12">
        <h6>role</h6>
        <p>This attribute is automatically rendered as role="dialog"</p>

        <h6>aria-hidden</h6>
        <p>This attribute is automatically rendered as aria-hidden="true"</p>

        <h6>aria-labelledby</h6>
        <p>Partial automatic support</p>
        <p>This attribute is automatically rendered as aria-labelledby="X", where "X" is a string composed of the value "modalTitle-" followed by a random number.</p>
        <p>This is only part of what is necessary though to achieve support for this Aria property.  The other part requires you to identify a section of text that serves as the label for this dialog and to give it the same id value assigned to the "aria-labelledby" attribute.</p>
        <p>To facilitate this, the "aria-labelledby" property is exposed on the sl-simple-modal component for use in your template.  <strong>Note:</strong> <a href="https://github.com/emberjs/ember.js/issues/4985">Issue 4985</a> (which was spawned from <a href="https://github.com/emberjs/ember.js/issues/2917">Issue 2987</a>) currently prevents accessing this property as expected or desired.  In order to access it in your template you must use:</p>
        <pre>\{{bind-attr id=_view.parentView.aria-labelledby}}</pre>
        <p>where you're having to use the private API property of "_view"</p>

        <h6>aria-describedby</h6>
        <p>There is no automatic support for this attribute</p>

        <hr>

        <h6>Advanced Implementation</h6>
